    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "ABOUT POLYMARKET\n\nPolymarket is the world's largest prediction market platform. We enable individuals to express views on real-world events by trading on outcomes across politics, economics, sports, culture, and current affairs. Built as a peer-to-peer marketplace with no centralized \"house,\" Polymarket aggregates diverse opinions into transparent, market-based probabilities that reflect collective expectations about the future.\n\nWe're growing fast – both in terms of volume ($21B traded in 2025) and adoption as an alternative news source. Our ambition is to become a ubiquitous beacon of truth in global media and we need your help adding fuel to the fire.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nYou're an engineer who builds things that make companies run faster. You see a manual process and your instinct is to automate it. You see a team bottleneck and you ship a tool to fix it — not next quarter, today.\n\nWe're hiring someone to own internal AI at Polymarket. You'll identify inefficiencies across every team, then build the agents, automations, and infrastructure to eliminate them. This is a hands-on-keyboard, high-autonomy role. You are the team.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Find the highest-leverage problems across ops, finance, talent, CX, engineering, and marketing — then build AI-powered systems to solve them\n\n - Design and deploy agents, copilots, and automations using LLMs, APIs, and whatever tools get the job done\n\n - Write production code. Python, TypeScript, integrations across our stack (Notion, Linear, Slack, GitHub, etc.)\n\n - Build shared infrastructure: prompt libraries, eval harnesses, agent frameworks, RAG pipelines\n\n - Move fast. You should be experimenting with new models and tooling within days of release\n\n - Set the standard for how the entire company builds with AI\n\n\nWHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR\n\n - Engineer first. You write production code daily. 5+ years building software\n\n - AI native. You live at the frontier — LLMs, agents, tool-use, evals, RAG. You don't just use AI tools, you build them\n\n - Founder energy. You've started something or operated like someone who has. End-to-end ownership, minimal direction\n\n - Shipping \u003e planning. You'd rather deploy something useful today than architect the perfect system for months\n\n - Full-stack. You can build the API, the UI, the pipeline, and the infra without waiting on anyone\n\n - Founded or co-founded a startup (a plus)\n\n - Open-source AI tooling contributions (a plus)\n\n - Crypto / fintech / prediction markets background (a plus)\n\n\nHOW TO APPLY\n\nResume, GitHub, and 2–3 AI systems you've built — show us the code and the impact.\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Competitive salary \u0026 equity\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - Full Health, Vision, \u0026 Dental coverage\n\n - 401k match\n\n - Hardware setup — new MacBook Pro, big display, \u0026 accessories\n\n\n",
